### INSTRUCTIONS
### ============================================

### How to use this file:
### 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VSCode
### 2. Open this file (test-registration.rest)
### 3. Click "Send Request" above any test
### 4. See response in new panel

### Expected Responses:
###
### ✅ 201 Created - User registered successfully
###    Response includes: id, name, email, age, createdAt
###
### ❌ 400 Bad Request - Error occurred
###    Response includes: error message explaining what went wrong
###
### ✅ 200 OK - Login successful
###    Response includes: user data and access token
###
### How to verify data:
### 1. Run: npm run drizzle:studio
### 2. Open: http://localhost:5555
### 3. Select "users" table from left sidebar
### 4. See all registered users with their data

### Troubleshooting:
###
### If "Cannot POST /api/v1/auth/register":
###   - Make sure server is running: npm run dev
###   - Check port is 8000 in .env (PORT=8000)
###
### If "Database connection refused":
###   - Check .env DATABASE_URL is correct
###   - Ensure migrations were applied: npm run drizzle:push
###
### If "User with this email already exists!":
###   - Use different email for new users
###   - Check Drizzle Studio to see existing users
###
### If "Name and email are required!":
###   - Make sure both "name" and "email" fields exist
###   - Both fields must have non-empty values
